---
import Main from "../layouts/Main.astro";
import aboutPhoto from "../assets/about.png";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import Button from "../components/Button.astro";

const containerLayout =
  "lg:grid lg:gap-6 lg:grid-cols-2 flex flex-col justify-start items-center";
const h1Styles =
  "text-lg py-6 font-serif font-semibold text-nowrap text-slate-700 italic lg:text-3xl";
---

<Main
  title="nathantranquilla.me | About Nathan Tranquilla"
  classes={`${containerLayout} w-full max-w-[1000px] mx-auto px-4 lg:my-10 my-4 mb-10 font-sans`}
>
  <h1 class={`${h1Styles} lg:hidden`}>About Nathan Tranquilla</h1>
  <figure
    class="flex h-full w-full flex-col items-center justify-start overflow-hidden lg:col-start-2 lg:col-end-3 lg:row-start-1 lg:pt-[7rem]"
  >
    <Image src={aboutPhoto} alt="Photo of Nathan" />
    <figcaption class="font-serif text-sm">
      Photos taken by Stephanie from <a
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
        href="https://magnoliacoastsphotography.com"
        class="cursor-pointer underline">Magnolia Coasts Photography</a
      >
    </figcaption>
  </figure>
  <article
    class="mb-auto flex flex-col items-start justify-start lg:col-start-1 lg:col-end-2 lg:row-start-1"
  >
    <h1 class={`${h1Styles} lg:block hidden`}>About Nathan Tranquilla</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-gray-700 lg:text-base">
      Nathan Tranquilla is spearheading a fundamental shift toward
      next-generation web development practices.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-gray-700 lg:text-base">
      At BlueSpurs, a small startup, Nathan built his first site in PHP for a
      local newspaper, immediately recognizing the compelling blend of art and
      logic that defines great web development. As JavaScript frameworks
      evolved, he positioned himself as an early adopter: mastering Backbone for
      improved structure, then React and Angular as they transformed the
      frontend landscape, consistently delivering fast, intuitive dashboards
      that exceeded both team and client expectations.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-gray-700 lg:text-base">
      With success came a critical realization. Rather than achieving the
      expected mastery, Nathan found himself spending more time circumventing
      tool limitations than building actual solutions. This led to a broader
      insight: the industry wasn't solving fundamental problemsâ€”it was simply
      becoming more sophisticated at managing inherent chaos.
    </p>
    <p
      class="col-start-1 col-end-2 row-start-1 mt-3 mb-10 text-sm leading-relaxed text-gray-700 lg:text-base"
    >
      Today, Nathan applies years of React expertise and deep JavaScript
      knowledge to pioneer Next-Gen Web Development. Drawing from extensive
      experience debugging complex state management, building scalable
      applications, and navigating JavaScript's intricacies, he's working to
      define a more robust, reliable, and developer-friendly future for web
      development.
    </p>
    <Button classes="mx-auto" href="/consultation"
      >Book A Consultation Today</Button
    >
  </article>
</Main>
